Package: ShinyState
Title: React-Style Hooks for Shiny Applications
Version: 0.7.0
Authors@R: person("Jesus", "Rodriguez Perez", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "rpsoft@gmail.com")
Description: A React- and Vue-inspired component and hook system for Shiny
    applications. Write components with useState(), useEffect(), useMemo(),
    useReducer(), computed values, lifecycle hooks, and watch(), instead of
    Shiny's reactive primitives. A client-side DOM-patching renderer preserves
    focus, cursor, and scroll across updates. Supports shared stores, child
    components with props, multi-page apps with a dormant tab lifecycle, and
    hash-based URL routing.
